The paper focuses on the modelling, verification, and analysis of wireless mesh network protocols, specifically the Ad hoc On-Demand Distance Vector (AODV) protocol. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of process algebra and formal methods for analysis also suggests a connection to computer science theory (cs.TH) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data structures and algorithms, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or systems and control (cs.SY).
